---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="What Decks Really Cost in Montgomery County (2026) | Belvedere Decks"
  description="Real 2026 deck pricing for Montgomery County, MD: composite deck refloor $14k–$20k, facelift $24k–$35k, custom decks $40k–$75k+. What moves the number and what a cheap bid leaves out."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Published pricing — 2026</p>
      <h1>What decks really cost in Montgomery County.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        Most deck companies won't put prices in writing until they've sat in your kitchen.
        Here's what projects actually run in Montgomery County in 2026.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Project</th><th>What it is</th><th>Typical range</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong><a href="/services/deck-refloor">Deck Refloor</a></strong></td>
            <td>Replacing just your deck boards with premium composite. Frame and railings stay.</td>
            <td>$14,000–$20,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong><a href="/services/deck-facelift">Deck Facelift</a></strong></td>
            <td>New boards, railings, and fascia on your existing frame.</td>
            <td>$24,000–$35,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong><a href="/services/custom-decks">Custom Deck</a></strong></td>
            <td>A fully custom new deck — engineered, permitted, and inspected.</td>
            <td>$40,000–$75,000+</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>What moves the number</h2>
      <p>
        Size. Board line — we install TimberTech and Trex, from entry to architectural grade.
        Railing choice. Stairs and lighting. Height off grade. And the one nobody mentions:
        the condition of your framing. That's why we inspect before we quote, and why our
        estimates include a stated allowance for joist replacement instead of a surprise
        change order later.
      </p>

      <h2>What should make you suspicious</h2>
      <p>
        A bid thousands below everyone else usually means no permit, no flashing membrane at
        the house, joists at the wrong spacing for composite boards, or railings screwed to
        deck boards instead of bolted to the frame. Those are exactly the things you can't
        see at the barbecue — and pay for in year five.
      </p>

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Every price we quote includes:</strong> code-depth footings, full ledger
        flashing, structural connectors with every fastener hole filled, permits and
        inspections where required, haul-away of all debris, and a 10-year written
        workmanship warranty on top of the 25–50-year manufacturer board warranties.
      </div>

      <h2>How our pricing compares</h2>
      <p>
        Bethesda's high-end design firms publish composite pricing starting around $30,000
        and running $120–180 per square foot installed. Budget operators advertise numbers
        that quietly exclude the structure. We land in between on purpose: premium
        specification at an honest number, with the math shown.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 24px;"><a class="btn primary" href="/contact">Get your exact price — same visit</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
